🔷 🔥 What is Exception Handling in MVC?

👉 When an error occurs (DB error, null, etc.)
👉 We handle it gracefully instead of showing crash/whitelabel page

🔴 Without Exception Handling
Whitelabel Error Page ❌

👉 Bad user experience

🔷 🔥 Types of Exception Handling in Spring MVC
Type	Use
Local (@ExceptionHandler)	Inside controller
Global (@ControllerAdvice)	For whole app ✅
Custom Exception	Business logic errors
🔷 🧩 1. LOCAL Exception Handling

👉 Inside same controller

@Controller
public class BookController {

    @ExceptionHandler(Exception.class)
    public String handleError(Exception ex, Model model) {

        model.addAttribute("msg", ex.getMessage());

        return "error";
    }
}
🔷 🧩 2. GLOBAL Exception Handling (BEST PRACTICE 🔥)

👉 Create a separate class

package com.rishav.web_mvc_book_app.exception;

import org.springframework.ui.Model;
import org.springframework.web.bind.annotation.*;

@ControllerAdvice
public class GlobalExceptionHandler {

    @ExceptionHandler(Exception.class)
    public String handleAllExceptions(Exception ex, Model model) {

        model.addAttribute("msg", "Something went wrong!");

        return "error"; // error.html
    }
}
